        "senderName": "NWS Spokane WA",
        "headline": "Frost Advisory issued June 7 at 11:39AM PDT until June 8 at 8:00AM PDT by NWS Spokane WA",
        "description": "* WHAT...Temperatures as low as 30 will result in frost formation.\n\n* WHERE...Springdale-Hunters Road, Sherman Pass, Winthrop,\nSchweitzer Mountain Road, Twisp, Tiger, Conconully, Republic,\nMethow, Kettle Falls, Wauconda, Fruitland, Orin-Rice Road, Priest\nRiver, Athol, Boulder Creek Road, Metaline Falls, Sandpoint, Clark\nFork, Bonners Ferry, Newport, Chewelah, Chesaw Road, Ione,\nMetaline, Eastport, Colville, Inchelium, Flowery Trail Road,\nMazama, Highway 20 Wauconda Summit, Loup Loup Pass, Deer Park, and\nNorthport.\n\n* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 8 AM PDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Frost could harm sensitive outdoor vegetation. Sensitive\noutdoor plants may be killed if left uncovered.",
        "instruction": "Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold.",
